<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="published records">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Published records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Widely distributed in Europe from south to north, however, it is very rare or regionally extinct in most parts of Central and Eastern Europe, while in the southwest and Western Europe it is quite widespread. It also occurs in the Middle East (Turkey and Iran), Caucasus and Siberia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="127 - 135" refId="B6" refString="Bogusch, P, 2018. Three new species and new records of cuckoo bees of the genus Epeolus in Turkey (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 58: 127 - 135, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" title="Three new species and new records of cuckoo bees of the genus Epeolus in Turkey (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" volume="58" year="2018">Bogusch 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 60" refId="B8" refString="Bogusch, P, Hadrava, J, 2018. The bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini) of Europe: taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology. Zootaxa 4437 (1): 1 - 60, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" title="The bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini) of Europe: taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" volume="4437" year="2018">Bogusch and Hadrava 2018</bibRefCitation>
). K. Warncke (unpublished data) reported this species also from the following localities in Turkey: Antakya, Bursa, Konya, Tuzlucz/Kars, 20 km north of Yuksekova. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="127 - 135" refId="B6" refString="Bogusch, P, 2018. Three new species and new records of cuckoo bees of the genus Epeolus in Turkey (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 58: 127 - 135, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" title="Three new species and new records of cuckoo bees of the genus Epeolus in Turkey (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/aemnp-2018-0010" volume="58" year="2018">Bogusch (2018)</bibRefCitation>
recorded known localities from Turkey.
</paragraph>
